                      Does ERA support animal rights?
                    </h5>
                    <div class="carrot"></div>
                  </header>
                  <div class="accord-content text-med-grey double-spaced">
                    <p>
                      Animal rights advocacy is based in the belief that animals should have inherent rights, such as the
                      right to life and the freedom to live as they wish. Conversely, animal welfare emphasizes making practical
                      improvements in the lives of animals while working within existing systems.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      Animal rights has brought attention to important ethical considerations, but it has also contributed to
                      challenges within the landscape of animal rescue. It is important to note that not all animal rights perspectives
                      contribute negatively to the animal welfare crisis. However, we believe that a more practical approach that focuses
                      on well-being and minimizing suffering will allow us to work more effectively to improve the lives of animals in
                      rescues and shelters.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </section>
